We can disable LLMNR in Group Policy by going to Computer Configuration --> Administrative Templates --> Network --> DNS Client and enabling "Turn OFF Multicast Name Resolution."


In the Local Group Policy Editor, double click on Startup, choose the PowerShell Scripts tab, and select "For this GPO, run scripts in the following order" to Run Windows PowerShell scripts first, and then click on Add and choose the script.
For these changes to occur, we would have to either reboot the target system or restart the network adapter.
  Scripts: 
    $regkey = "HKLM:SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\services\NetBT\Parameters\Interfaces"
    Get-ChildItem $regkey |foreach { Set-ItemProperty -Path "$regkey\$($_.pschildname)" -Name NetbiosOptions -Value 2 -Verbose}
